HEADWORD: Catalepsis
<hw>Cat`a*lep"sis</hw>
<pr>(?)</pr>, }</mhw> <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[NL. <ets>catalepsis</ets>, fr.
Gr. <?/ a seizure, fr. <?/ to seize upon; <grk>kata`</grk> down + <?/ to
take, seize.]</ety> <fld>(Med.)</fld> <def>A sudden suspension of
sensation and volition, the body and limbs preserving the position that
may be given them, while the action of the heart and lungs
continues.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Cataleptic</ent>⟦br⟧
